1.00	Egely_Monastery	Egely Monastery	Egely Monastery - Taikyo-ji is a Buddhist monastery, formerly in the Rinzai Zen tradition, founded by Denko John Mortensen on the Danish island of Bornholm in 2007. Located in an old farmhouse and cowshed, it was the only Rinzai Zen monastery in Scandinavia with Zen teacher in permanent residence.	
